SYNOPSIS

After a tragedy, 16-year-old Gracie (Carly Shroeder) channels her grief by fighting to get girls onto the varsity soccer field in this inspiring drama set in the 1970s.  Passionate and strong-willed, Gracie is blocked from all sides as she argues the rights of women to play competitive soccer.  The film is based on the real-life story of actress Elizabeth Shue (who plays Gracie's mom), who championed the cause of women's sports as a teenager.
